<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="32" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1449,2036]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,330,1529,1555]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Etymology</emphasis>
. A combination of the Latin words: longus and barba, referring to the long filar-like processes of aedeagus.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="32" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1449,2036]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,325,1609,1635]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Fore tarsomeres with longer fringe-like setae on anterior surface; surstylus deeply bifurcated distally, with minute scale-like processes (Fig. 
<number box="[709,741,1650,1676]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" value="13.0">13</number>
); aedeagus with 
<number box="[941,956,1650,1676]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" value="4.0">4</number>
pairs of rod-like processes, one of them twice as long as others (Fig. 
<number box="[486,519,1690,1716]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" value="14.0">14</number>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="33" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1449,2036]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,341,1729,1755]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32">Description</emphasis>
. Male. Frons and fronto-orbital plate brown. Palpus black. Mesonotum and scutellum yellow brown, without patches and longitudinal stripes. Postpronotal lobe yellow brown on upper 
<number box="[1210,1224,1770,1796]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[1234,1249,1770,1796]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" value="5.0">5</number>
, white on lower 
<number box="[151,167,1810,1836]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" value="2.0">2</number>
/ 
<number box="[177,191,1810,1836]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" value="5.0">5</number>
. Katepisternum nearly brown. Legs almost brown, pale on all tarsomeres. Fore femur with 
<number box="[1312,1327,1810,1836]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" value="4.0">4</number>
setae on median of ventral surface; fore tarsomeres with longer fringe-like setae on anterior surface. Abdominal all tergites and sternites brown. Cercus with sporadic pubescence (Fig. 
<number box="[949,982,1890,1916]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" value="12.0">12</number>
). Plate between hypandrium and aedeagus with a few pubescence (Fig. 
<number box="[549,581,1930,1956]" pageId="5" pageNumber="32" value="14.0">14</number>
).
</paragraph>
